
[1]intendant

   INTEND'ANT, n. [L. intendo.]

   1. One who has the charge, oversight, direction or management of some
   public business; as an intendant of marine; as intendant of finance; a
   word much used in France, and sometimes in England and America, but we
   generally use in lieu of it superintendent.

   2. In Charleston, S. Carolina, the mayor or chief municipal officer of
   the city.
